On the right hand side of the page, instead of finding friends by clicking on the friends link, it would be advisable to make a drop down for the friends available in the list. So that, when one hovers over the link, the drop down of friends would appear which in my opinion would make transferring money time efficient. Secondly the settings link at the top right hand corner could be replaced by messages link which would let us know whether the cash has been successfully transferred or not.
Some currency image would have shown on the top to make them understand that it is related to money

The picture colour is not clear.If the colour of the picture is clear, the design will be very good.There are only 2 to 3 colours in the design, the number of colours can be improved to make the design attractive.

Seems to be very utilitarian. There is very little in the way of aesthetics on  the page, and maybe that is the intent. I'm assuming the pictures are blanked out for the purposes of the study only, but it would probably affect the interpretation of the page in a positive way if we could see how the pictures enhance the page. Color scheme is somewhat bland.

I would like to see, on this page, pending payments (from me and due to me) tied to calendar events. Also, need the ability to split a specific payment amount among a group of friends equally, without having to calculate that myself. Also, I hope that when friend X pays friend Y for something, my ability to see it is governed by privacy settings - e.g. I am able to see above who paid to whom, when I am not part of that transaction.

I like the overall layout of the page. I think I would like it more with a little more color.

At the top right, I would add a section called "Account." I would like to be able to see where I have sent my money and what money was sent to me. Settings to me just makes me think about making the interface look different. Also, maybe you can mention what type of payment it is. Is it USD, or Euro, etc. Overall, it's a very simple and clean interface. I really like it.

The design is fair.  I don't see anything that shows how secure your payment is.  I would be very scared to use this app to transfer money to someone.  It doesn't really show how much money was transferred each time either.  It looks more like a facebook page than an app to transfer money.  I think it needs to look more secure and provide signs of security and amounts of transactions.  It looks more like a social app for friends to talk.

The design very much looks like Facebook but in a different type of blue color. The word "paid" looks fine but "charged" doesn't really sound good. "Charged" should be replaced with something else, like repaid or reimbursed. It doesn't look cool to take up so much space for the "Invite Friends" option, Instead, it should just be in a single line like "Invite Friends?".

I'm a big fan of the design. Very simple, straight forward, and user-friendly. Everything is self explanatory. While the design is 'fun,' it isn't childish. I feel like, with a lot of "new" apps & websites, this is a hard thing to balance for companies/designers. A lot of times companies try to go with a 'fun' design that [in my opinion] ends up looking very child-like. With a design like seen above, I could see all age groups being interested/comfortable with the overall feel.
the design looks clean and well thought out

I think that I would like to have more information on the sidebar about what's pending and what has been spent, but other than that, this is actually really neat. I could easily see using this much more than Paypal.
